Description: Three joining fragments of rim and body of pottery eye cup; interior: glazed with one added red band lined in white; exterior: top of rim glazed; below, a pair of large eyes with arching eyebrows and spiral forms to denote the nose; two bands below the handle zone.
Bibliographic references: Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (p. 256, no. 7)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.468)
